I have fixed the compilation error by resolving a dependency mismatch in `pay-adminusers/pom.xml`. The project now compiles and passes all tests.

The error `cannot access org.slf4j.spi.LoggingEventAware` was caused by `logback-classic` version `1.4.1` depending on SLF4J 2.x interfaces, while the project uses `slf4j-api` version `1.7.36`. I downgraded `logback-classic` to `1.2.11` to ensure compatibility.

**Verification:**
- `mvn clean test-compile` passed.
- `mvn test` passed (757 tests run, 0 failures).

Since the error was a configuration issue rather than a source code logic error, a Spoon source code transformation was not the appropriate solution. The build is now fixed.

